trials.freeResponse: Sometimes blickets will squeak. They are yellow and appear to have a crystal like structure.
Tomas usually click and appear to be cone shaped.
We encountered a daxes that beeped, it is unknown whether any others share this phenomenon. They appear to be red and cylindrical.
Wugs often boom. They are cyan cubes.
We heard one griffs whistle. We are unsure if any more will. They appear to be purple.
Feps usually ring and are red.
